Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs and beat well. Add flour, baking soda, and salt. Mix well. Stir in oatmeal, apricots, and sunflower seeds. Shape into 1 inch balls. Place on lightly greased cookie sheet. Flatten each cookie with the bottom of a glass or jar. Bake 10-12 minutes. Store airtight or freeze.